caption:
08 - The evolved form of Bryk. Still just a dynamite design.

Pokedex: After a struggle of wills one Bryk climbs atop another and assumes control of their new form, one that is twice as heavy and even more unwieldy than before. The consciousness of the lower Bryk is now trapped inside a body with no sense of time or space, a void of eternal hopeless darkness. Enjoy, kids.

body:
Ghost type Pokémon

So you know how a lot of Ghost types are said to feed on negative emotions?

What if they LITERALLY DO. What if their ecological niche is spiritual decomposers/scavengers. They eat the hatred and dread and sadness before it spreads.

What I’m getting at is Shuppets licking you would help you feel less sad and that’s cute.

summary:
Broke: Making Pokémon "realistic" by saying "WELL SCIENTIFICALLY--"
Woke: Making Pokémon realistic by accepting all the weird...
body:
Broke: Making Pokémon “realistic” by saying “WELL SCIENTIFICALLY–”

Woke: Making Pokémon realistic by accepting all the weird shit they do, even if there’s no scientific, symbolic, or mythological basis but giving them real-world implications. Charizard is clearly a predator species so it likely hunts smaller pokemon. Maybe it cooks them before eating them with its fire breath?
